5061	[Kernel comparison: the localised global equalizer matches the \(D(f)\)-cover equalizer]
5062	  \label{lem:qcoh_section_kernel_comparison}
5063	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.qcoh_section_kernel_comparison}
5064	  \uses{lem:qcoh_section_isLocalizedModule, lem:isLocalizedModule_linearEquiv_mathlib}
5065	  % NOTE: packaged-iso corollary of the keystone. In Lean this declaration is
5066	  % `IsLocalizedModule.iso ρ_f`, derived in one line from lem:qcoh_section_isLocalizedModule; its only
5067	  % real dependency is the keystone (plus the Mathlib `IsLocalizedModule.iso`/`.linearEquiv` packaging,
5068	  % lem:isLocalizedModule_linearEquiv_mathlib). The full equalizer→match→kernel-comparison chase lives in
5069	  % the keystone proof block, where it belongs; this block is now the short downstream corollary.
5070	  Let \(X = \Spec R\), let \(\mathcal{F}\) be a quasi-coherent \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-module, let \(f \in R\),
5071	  and let \(g_1, \ldots, g_n\) be the finite presentation cover of
5072	  Lemma~\ref{lem:qcoh_finite_presentation_cover}, with \(\operatorname{span}\{g_j\} = R\). Then the
5073	  canonical \(R\)-linear map \(\Gamma(X, \mathcal{F})_f \to \Gamma(D(f), \mathcal{F})\) induced by
5074	  \(\rho_f : \Gamma(X, \mathcal{F}) \to \Gamma(D(f), \mathcal{F})\) (the localisation lift of \(\rho_f\)
5075	  at the powers of \(f\)) is an isomorphism.
5076	\end{lemma}
